public class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int i = 0;

        while (i < n) {
            if (nums[i] == target) {
                return i;
            } else if (nums[i] > target) {
                return i;
            }
            i++;
        }

        return n;
    }
}
```

This code implements the binary search algorithm to find the index of the target element in the array. If the target element is not found, it returns the index where the target element should be inserted to maintain the sorted order of the array.
